<section id="candidates">
    <title>Translation Candidates Module</title>

    <section>
        <title>Introduction</title>

    <para>The source text of a document can be pre-processed against various translation resources
        (TM, MT, etc.) to provide translation candidates. This module provides an XLIFF capability to store lists of
        possible translations along with information about the similarity of the match, the quality
        of the translation, its provenance, etc. </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Namespace and Validation Artifacts</title>
        <para>The namespace for the Translation Candidates module is: <code>urn:oasis:names:tc:xliff:matches:2.0</code></para>
        <para>Schema and Schematron for this module are available at <ulink
                url="&this-loc;/schemas/matches.xsd"
                >&this-loc;/schemas/matches.xsd</ulink> and <ulink
                    url="&this-loc;/schemas/matches.sch"
                    >&this-loc;/schemas/matches.sch</ulink>.</para>


    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Fragment Identification Prefix</title>
        <para>The fragment identification prefix for the Translation Candidates module is:
                <code>mtc</code></para>
    </section>

    <section id="mtc_CoreReuse">
        <title>XLIFF Core Reuse</title>
        <para>The <link linkend="candidates">Translation Candidates Module</link> reuses several <firstterm>XLIFF Core</firstterm> elements, most of them have mandatory <olink targetdoc="../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"><code>xlf:id</code></olink>. The uniqueness scopes for the reused <olink targetdoc="../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"><code>xlf:id</code></olink> attributes are separate from the <firstterm>XLIFF Core</firstterm>. The following states the exact normative Constraints for the validation purposes:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <title>Constraints</title>
            <listitem>
                <para> When the <olink targetdoc="../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"
                    ><code>xlf:id</code></olink> attribute is used on <olink
                                targetdoc="../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
                                ><code>&lt;xlf:mrk&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sm.xml"
                                    targetptr="sm"><code>&lt;xlf:sm&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                                        targetdoc="../elements/inline/pc.xml" targetptr="pc"
                                        ><code>&lt;xlf:pc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sc.xml"
                                            targetptr="sc"><code>&lt;xlf:sc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                                                targetdoc="../elements/inline/ec.xml" targetptr="ec"
                                                ><code>&lt;xlf:ec&gt;</code></olink>, or <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/ph.xml"
                                                    targetptr="ph"><code>&lt;xlf:ph&gt;</code></olink> elements reused within the <link
                                                        linkend="candidates">Translation Candidates Module</link>:</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem><para>The inline elements enclosed by a <olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/target.xml"
                        targetptr="target"><code>&lt;xlf:target></code></olink> element
                        <glossterm>must</glossterm> use the duplicate <olink
                            targetdoc="../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"><code>xlf:id</code></olink> values
                        of their corresponding inline elements enclosed within the sibling <olink
                            targetdoc="../elements/structural/source.xml" targetptr="source"
                            ><code>&lt;xlf:source></code></olink> element if and only if those corresponding
                        elements exist.</para></listitem>

                    <listitem><para>Except for the above exception, the value <glossterm>must</glossterm> be unique among all of the above within the
                        enclosing <olink targetdoc="../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"><code>&lt;match></code></olink>
                        element.
                    </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>When used on <olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/data.xml"
                    targetptr="data"><code>&lt;xlf:data></code></olink> elements reused within the <link
                        linkend="candidates">Translation Candidates Module</link>:</para>
                <para>The value <glossterm>must</glossterm> be unique among all <olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/data.xml"
                    targetptr="data"><code>&lt;xlf:data></code></olink> <code>xlf:id</code> attribute values within the enclosing
                    <olink targetdoc="../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"><code>&lt;match></code></olink> element.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>When the <olink targetdoc="../attributes/dataref.xml" targetptr="dataref"
                    ><code>xlf:dataRef</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../attributes/datarefstart.xml"
                        targetptr="datarefstart"><code>xlf:datarefstart</code></olink>, and <olink
                            targetdoc="../attributes/datarefend.xml" targetptr="datarefend"
                            ><code>xlf:dataRefEnd</code></olink> attributes are used on <olink
                                targetdoc="../elements/inline/pc.xml" targetptr="pc"
                                ><code>&lt;xlf:pc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sc.xml"
                                    targetptr="sc"><code>&lt;xlf:sc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                                        targetdoc="../elements/inline/ec.xml" targetptr="ec"
                                        ><code>&lt;xlf:ec&gt;</code></olink>, or <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/ph.xml"
                                            targetptr="ph"><code>&lt;xlf:ph&gt;</code></olink> elements reused within the <link
                                                linkend="candidates">Translation Candidates Module</link>, their
                    <code>NMTOKEN</code> values <glossterm>must</glossterm> identify <olink
                        targetdoc="../elements/structural/data.xml" targetptr="data"
                        ><code>&lt;data&gt;</code></olink> elements within the enclosing <olink
                            targetdoc="../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                            ><code>&lt;match></code></olink> element. Those attributes <glossterm>must
                                not</glossterm> be used without corresponding <olink
                                    targetdoc="../elements/structural/data.xml" targetptr="data"
                                    ><code>&lt;data&gt;</code></olink> elements within the enclosing <olink
                                        targetdoc="../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                                        ><code>&lt;match></code></olink> element.  </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </section>

    <section id="matchAnnotation">
        <title>Translation Candidate Annotation</title>

        <para>This annotation can be used to mark up the scope of a translation candidate within the
            content of a unit. This module can reference any source or even target spans of content
            that are referencable via the XLIFF <olink targetdoc="../../fragments/fragments.xml"
                targetptr="fragid">Fragment Identification</olink> mechanism, however in case the
            corresponding fragment is not suitably delimited, the best way how to mark the relevant
            span is to use the following annotation.</para>

        <para>Usage:</para>

        <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
            <listitem>
                <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/id.xml"
                    targetptr="id"><code>id</code></olink> attribute is
                    <glossterm>required</glossterm></para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/type.xml" targetptr="type"
                            ><code>type</code></olink> attribute is <glossterm>required</glossterm>
                    and set to <code>mtc:match</code></para>
            </listitem>


            <listitem>
                <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/ref.xml" targetptr="ref"
                            ><code>ref</code></olink> attribute is not used.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/translate.xml" targetptr="translate"
                            ><code>translate</code></olink> attribute is
                        <glossterm>optional</glossterm></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

        <para>For example:</para>

        <programlisting>
&lt;unit id="1"&gt;
  &lt;mtc:matches&gt;
    &lt;mtc:match ref="#m1"&gt;
      &lt;source&gt;He is my friend.&lt;/source&gt;
      &lt;target&gt;Il est mon ami.&lt;/target&gt;
    &lt;/mtc:match&gt;
    &lt;mtc:match ref="#m1"&gt;
      &lt;source&gt;He is my best friend.&lt;/source&gt;
      &lt;target&gt;Il est mon meilleur ami.&lt;/target&gt;
    &lt;/mtc:match&gt;
  &lt;/mtc:matches&gt;
  &lt;segment&gt;
    &lt;source&gt;&lt;mrk id="m1" type="mtc:match"&gt;He is my friend.&lt;/mrk&gt;&lt;/source&gt;
  &lt;/segment&gt;
  &lt;segment&gt;
    &lt;source&gt;Yet, I barely see him.&lt;/source&gt;
  &lt;/segment&gt;
&lt;/unit&gt;
</programlisting>
    </section>

